      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(minimax): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nBound MiniMax provider HTTP response reads using shared provider helpers\nto prevent unbounded buffering from untrusted upstream JSON bodies.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/minimax/oauth.ts` | Use `readProviderJsonResponse` for auth code JSON (1 MiB cap) |\n| `extensions/minimax/video-generation-provider.ts` | Use `readProviderJsonResponse` for poll/metadata/submit JSON (1 MiB cap). Download paths keep `readResponseWithLimit` with configurable caps. |\n| `extensions/minimax/image-generation-provider.ts` | Already uses `readProviderJsonResponse` — unchanged |\n| `extensions/minimax/tts.ts` | Already uses `readProviderJsonResponse` — unchanged |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof: bounded reader cancels oversized stream at 1 MiB\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_minimax_bound.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: bytesSent=1048576 (cap=1048576, would-stream=67108864)\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Unit tests\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/\n Test Files  10 passed | 1 failed (11)\n      Tests  134 passed | 2 failed (136)\n```\n\nThe 2 failures are Windows `EBUSY` file-lock errors on temp SQLite files, unrelated to this change.\n\n### Design\n\nJSON paths use `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared provider contract) where the caller consumes parsed JSON. Download paths keep the raw `readResponseWithLimit` with configurable per-request caps.\n\n_AI-assisted._",
